\f0\b\fs40 \cf0 CSS animation:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs26 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 On the element itself you place the
\f0\b  transition parameter 
\f1\b0 \
#glass \{\
transition-property: transform;\
  transition-duration: 3s;\
  transition-timing-function: ease-in-out;\
  transition-delay: 1s;\
\}\
\

\f0\b Or the shorthand: 
\f1\b0 transition: transform 3s ease-in-out 1s;\
\
On the trigger you place the
\f0\b  transform parameter\
 
\f1\b0 #glass:hover \{\
  transform: scale(50%);\
\}\
\
You may also have different property by separating each of them with a coma (,)\
\
#glass \{\
 transition: transform 0.5s ease-in-out 1s, filter 0.5s ease 0.7s;\
\}\
\
#glass:hover \{\
 transform: scale(200%);\
 filter: blur(10px);\
\}\
\

\f0\b Or using all 
\f1\b0 if they all have similar values \
 transition: all 0.5s ease-in-out 1s;\
\
\
You may use 
\f0\b animation
\f1\b0  and 
\f0\b keyframe
\f1\b0  if you want that to go continuously \
#glass \{\
  position: absolute;\
  top: 45%;                  /* ajustement pour la main */\
  left: 35%;\
  width: 6%;\
  height: auto;\
  cursor: pointer;\
  animation: glassDance 2s ease-in-out infinite;\
\}\
\
@keyframes glassDance \{\
  0%, 100% \{\
    transform: scale(100%);\
    filter: blur(0);\
  \}\
  50% \{\
    transform: scale(200%);\
    filter: blur(10px);\
  \}\
\}\
\
\
Try this one and the element will dance:\
1st, on the element: animation: dance 2s infinite ease-in-out;\
\
2nd, on the @keyframe:\
0% \{\
    transform: translateX(0) rotate(0deg);\
  \}\
  20% \{\
    transform: translateX(-20px) rotate(-5deg);\
  \}\
  40% \{\
    transform: translateX(20px) rotate(5deg);\
  \}\
  60% \{\
    transform: translateY(-20px) scale(1.05);\
  \}\
  80% \{\
    transform: translateX(-10px) rotate(-3deg);\
  \}\
  100% \{\
    transform: translateX(0) rotate(0deg);\
  \}\
\
Ps: animation will always take over on rollover. So :hover won\'92t work at the same time as animation. But a quick workaround is to paused animation at : hover with simply that :   animation-play-state: paused;   and then have the transformation\
\
#mench-all:hover \{\
  animation-play-state: paused;          \
  transform: translateX(100px) rotate(180deg);\
     \
\}\
\
